description: Attempting to meet demand by executive personnel for direct travel to and from sites within planetary atmospheres that did not compromise on comfort, Van Hummel rushed to put the Chariot on the market in 2072. Fitting a CEO-rated passenger cabin and lounge with built-in bar into such a compact, reactor-powered design was no easy task however. With only minimal crew accomodations, this resulted in the sole pilot also having to serve as steward for their passenger.
